            "text": "reductio ad absurdum",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " If it be a shame for a woman to be shorn or shaven.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " When a woman was tried by \"the ordeal of the water of jealousy,\" her head was uncovered by the priest (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 5:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). To be shorn or shaven was a sign of mourning (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 21:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and was a disgrace inflicted on adulteresses. 1 Corinthians 11:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
